 senior management and executive experience in the mobile gaming and content sectors his primary areas of focus on delivering the strategy of monstermob group new global initiatives and the integration of acquisitions prior to joining monstermob he worked for jp morgan in both the debt capital markets and mergers and acquisitions teams within the media technology and telecoms tmt division he began his career as a physicist at siemens solar and within the strategic planning and development divisions of technicolor working for the chief operating officer on a range of acquisitions and initiatives worldwide he served as the interim chairman of glu mobile inc since july  mr de masi serves as member of advisory board at blockchain capital he has been a director of glu mobile inc since january   he has been director at plain vanilla corp since january  he served as a director of xura inc since november   until august   he serves as a director of agnitio capital limited he served as a director of monstermob group plc he has published a number of research papers on semiconductor technologies mr de masi holds a ba and an ma in physics and a master of science in electronic engineering from cambridge universityread full background corporate headquarters  howard streetsan francisco california united statesphone fax  board members memberships directoragnitio capital limitedpresentexecutive chairmanglu mobile incpresentdirectorplain vanilla corp education ma university of cambridgems university of cambridgeba university of cambridge other affiliations handson mobile incarc associatesuniversity of cambridgemonstermob group plcmavenir systemsagnitio capital limitedplain vanilla corpblockchain capital annual compensation salarytotal annual compensation stocks options all other compensationexercised optionsexercised options valueexercisable optionsunexercisable optionstotal value of optionstotal number of options total compensation total annual cash compensationtotal short term compe